    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available now is a driver-focused E92 M3, powered by the S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8 featuring individual throttle bodies and an 8,400 RPM redline. This unit is equipped with a tactile 6-speed manual transmission and the M Variable Differential Lock for optimal torque distribution. The chassis remains sharp, utilizing Electronic Damping Control (EDC) and a multi-link rear suspension geometry that retains its factory-spec rigidity. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed, including a recent rod bearing service and throttle actuator replacement, ensuring the longevity of the high-tension rotating assembly. This is a mechanically sound example of the last atmospheric M-car, offering an analog connection and a linear power band that modern turbocharged platforms cannot replicate.",
